sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: NemR URep
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A construct created to test the effectiveness of the NemR upstream intergenic region (BBa_1398005). The construct contains the entire NemR upstream region (BBa_1398005), which contains a promoter and RBS. It is followed by the fluorescent reporter iLOV (listed in the repository as BBa_K660004), a double STOP codon and a double terminator (B0015).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Exeter iGEM 2014
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The origin of this region is Escherichia coli JD22799. The regulatory sequences were acquired from the iGEM repository.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: iLOV was used as a reporter in this construct as it ???outperforms??? GFP.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K660004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: iLOV has the same function and uses as LOV2. As a reporter, it is advantageous over GFP derived fluorescent proteins due to its small size (useful if you are tagging proteins), ability to recover quickly from photobleaching and use in anoxic conditions.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Glasgow Uni 2011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: iLOV is a version of LOV2 that has been altered through site directed mutagenesis and DNA shuffling.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: illegal restriction sites. The part was synthesized to remove them.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: NemR (UIR)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This sequence is found upstream of several NemR regulated genes. It was created for use as a TNT-detection mechanism. It contains the bases from X+ to the start codon, which include a promoter and RBS. This region should allow regulation of gene preoducts through the detection of TNT. If it is not present NemR will bind to a specified sequence of bases and inhibit transcription. If TNT is not present NemR will not bind and transcription will complete.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Exeter iGEM 2014
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The origin of this region is Escherichia coli JD22799.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: When studied using bioinformatic databases, such as BLAST, the start codon is incorrectly labelled at position X+. The start codon is correctly positioned at the end of this sequence.
